# Named Constructor Parameters

Category: Flutter
Status: 🟢 Accepted
Version: 0.1
Date: 2026-07-14

---

## Decision

Use named parameters for constructors throughout the project.

---

## Reason

- Improves readability.
- Prevents parameter order mistakes.
- Makes object creation self-documenting.
- Easier to maintain as models grow.

---

## Alternatives Considered

- Positional parameters.

---

## Consequences

Positive

- Clearer code.
- Easier maintenance.
- Safer when multiple parameters share the same type.

Negative

- Slightly more typing.

